bib.title: Optimized polarimetry for polarization-transfer experiments with protons and deuterons.

free_txt: SD:Updated to new date formats,lower case.
MONITOR was added. BIB was updated. REACTION code in
Subents 002,003 corrected. Author's name corrected
(Neiben -> Neissen).
The reactions He-4(p,p)He-4,C-12(p,p)C-12 and
He-3(d,p)He-4 are used as analyzers.The new polarimeter
was used for a measurement of the polarization-transfer
coefficients K(Y) and K(z) of the reaction D(p,p)D at
E(p)=19 MeV.
The number of counts in the elastic peak was corrected
for background and deadtime.
Four pairs of silicon surface barrier detectors
mounted symmetrically to the beam axis.
An additional detector mounted at 20.degr.(lab) was
used as a target thickness monitor.
Uncertainty in carbon peak separation
from oxygen peak.
The errors due to geometrical
uncertainties of the polarimeter and detector setup
and of the beam position
Tabulated data were obtained from NNDC
Uncertainty in effective target thickness
The errors are the algebraic sum of the
systematic and statistical errors
Angle at lab.system
99.99% isotopically pure 12CH(4) gas target was used.
total errors between 4% and 6% in cross section
A self-supporting C-12 foil with a thickness of
approximately 100 mug/cm**2 was used.
